  • Field Details

    • OPTIONS_ID

      static final UUID OPTIONS_ID
      Unique identifier for this class of options. Always refer to this field by name and not by its value to ensure compatibility when the codebase is updated as the value of the field may change!

    • BOUNDS

      static final MixedDataKey<ILatLngBounds> BOUNDS
      The bounds of the rectangle

    • CLICKABLE

      static final MixedDataKey<Boolean> CLICKABLE
      Indicates whether this Rectangle handles mouse events. Defaults to true.

    • DRAGGABLE

      static final MixedDataKey<Boolean> DRAGGABLE
      If set to true, the user can drag this rectangle over the map. Defaults to false.

    • EDITABLE

      static final MixedDataKey<Boolean> EDITABLE
      If set to true, the user can edit this rectangle by dragging the control points shown at the corners and on each edge. Defaults to false.

    • FILL_COLOR

      static final MixedDataKey<String> FILL_COLOR
      The fill color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

    • FILL_OPACITY

      static final MixedDataKey<Double> FILL_OPACITY
      The fill opacity between 0.0 and 1.0

    • STROKE_COLOR

      static final MixedDataKey<String> STROKE_COLOR
      The stroke color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

    • STROKE_OPACITY

      static final MixedDataKey<Double> STROKE_OPACITY
      The stroke opacity between 0.0 and 1.0

    • STROKE_POSITION

      static final MixedDataKey<StrokePosition> STROKE_POSITION
      The stroke position. Defaults to StrokePosition.CENTER. This property is not supported on Internet Explorer 8 and earlier.

    • STROKE_WEIGHT

      static final MixedDataKey<Integer> STROKE_WEIGHT
      The stroke width in pixels.

    • VISIBLE

      static final MixedDataKey<Boolean> VISIBLE
      Whether this rectangle is visible on the map. Defaults to true.

    • ZINDEX

      static final MixedDataKey<Double> ZINDEX
      The zIndex compared to other polys.

      static IOptionsFiller makeOptionsFiller(ICefUtils cefUtils)
      *FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY!!* OWLMAPS DEVELOPER CODE SHOULD *NOT* USE THIS METHOD! Factory to create the IOptionsFiller that converts the component options into their corresponding Javascript Google Map component options.
